    {front:"Iron deficiency — blood smear and treatment", back:"Smear: microcytic hypochromic cells with anisocytosis (high RDW) and poikilocytosis (pencil cells, cigar cells), often with thrombocytosis. Treatment: PO iron for at least 3 months (causes GI symptoms; take pre-meal with water/orange juice) or IV iron if PO is not tolerated (risk of allergic reaction, GI symptoms, arthralgia)."}
